      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Most urban planners view congestion pricing as a critical climate tool, but they universally agree it must be paired with aggressive transit investment to avoid widening economic inequality. While the environmental benefits are undeniable, professional circles remain deeply divided on whether the revenue generated is sufficient to justify the long-term economic costs for marginalized neighborhoods and low-income commuters. The consensus is shifting toward a hybrid model where pricing is paired with guaranteed free transit passes for those unable to afford it, rather than treating the fee as a standalone policy solution.",
